BIB                  6         15
REACTION   (8-O-16(N,P)7-N-16,,SIG,,FIS)
DETECTOR   (SCIN) An anthracene scintillation detector has been
           used to measure the gamma-ray dose rate at a given
           distance along the centerline of the source coil in
           air.
METHOD     Decay constant used is 0.0943 sec**-1.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The error quoted does not include any
           uncertainty in the decay scheme, the dose-to-flux
           conversion factor and the energy response of the
           detector. The major portion of the error is
           associated with an assumed maximum uncertainty of 1 sec
            in the transport time of the water through the system.
CORRECTION The observed dose rate is corrected for background
           and the O19 contribution.
