BIB                  5         15
REACTION   (8-O-17(N,P)7-N-17,,SIG,,FIS)
DETECTOR   (LONGC) A "long counter" has been used to measure the
           fast neutron flux along the centerline of the source
           coil in air. The "long counter" measures fast
           neutron flux independent of the neutron energy
           between 0.5 Mev and 3.0 Mev. This detector has been
           calibrated with a Ra-Be and a Po-Be neutron source
           of known source strengths.
METHOD     Decay constant used is 0.167 sec**-1.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The error quoted does not include any
           uncertainty in the decay scheme and the energy
           response of the detector. The major portion of the
           error is associated with the uncertainty of the
           transport time of the water through the system.
